      "author": "Moonjuun",
      "description": "## Highlights\n\n**Graph-view clustering via hierarchical tags.** VoxNote-generated notes used to drift across Obsidian's graph view as isolated STT↔summary pairs with no shared key. This release adds a hierarchical tag to every generated note so the shared `voxnote` parent becomes an automatic hub:\n\n| Note kind | Tag |\n|---|---|\n| STT transcript | `voxnote/transcript` |\n| AI summary | `voxnote/summary` |\n| Vault guide docs (`VoxNote/README.md` · `FEATURES.md`) | `voxnote/docs` |\n\n```\n       #voxnote (hub)\n        ├── #voxnote/transcript ── STT notes\n        ├── #voxnote/summary    ── AI summary notes\n        └── #voxnote/docs       ── README · FEATURES (guides)\n```\n\nThe summary → STT backlink (`source` frontmatter + body `> Source: [[…]]`) keeps a single session's pair tightly joined, so the graph now reads as \"one hub, one branch per session\" instead of scattered isolated pairs.\n\n### Hide the guide docs from graph view (optional)\n\nThe auto-seeded vault README/FEATURES are static documentation — not session output. If you don't want them in your graph, add this one-liner to **Settings → Graph view → Filters → Search**:\n\n```\n-tag:#voxnote/docs\n```\n\n### Breaking-ish: STT default-template tags changed\n\nThe STT default template's previous tag set `[meeting, stt]` is replaced by the single hierarchical tag `[voxnote/transcript]`. If you relied on `#meeting` or `#stt` for your own workflows, layer them back in your own template — clustering still works as long as the hierarchical tag is present.\n\n### Existing notes\n\nExisting notes are **not migrated** — only newly created notes pick up the new tag scheme. The auto-seeded `VoxNote/README.md` / `VoxNote/FEATURES.md` are only installed once and are not re-installed if they already exist; older copies have no frontmatter. To back-fill, see the new \"Graph-view clustering\" section in `FEATURES.md`.\n\n## Install\n\nSettings → Community plugins → search \"VoxNote\" → Install / Update.\n\nManual install: drop `main.js`, `manifest.json`, `styles.css` into `<vault>/.obsidian/plugins/voxnote/` and reload Obsidian.",
